ESSAY_1772831223_108	1	Computers have become an integral part of modern life, influencing how we work, learn, and communicate. While some argue that increased computer usage has negative effects on society, I believe the benefits far outweigh the drawbacks. Computers enable access to vast amounts of information, facilitate global communication, and improve productivity in virtually every field. In education, computers provide students with interactive learning tools and access to online resources that were previously unavailable. Students can research topics, collaborate with peers across the world, and develop technical skills that are essential in today workforce. Furthermore, computers have revolutionized healthcare through advanced diagnostic tools, electronic medical records, and telemedicine capabilities. However, it is important to acknowledge the challenges that come with widespread computer use. Issues such as screen addiction, cyberbullying, and privacy concerns are real problems that society must address. Despite these challenges, the solution is not to reduce computer usage but to promote responsible and educated use of technology. In conclusion, computers are a powerful tool that, when used wisely, can greatly enhance our quality of life and drive progress in countless areas.	4	The essay scored 4 out of 6 mainly because it starts off strongly with a clear thesis statement and effectively lists the benefits of computers in education, communication, and productivity. However, the essay falls short of a higher score due to its abrupt conclusion (missing the word "skills") and overall lack of supporting details and nuanced exploration of potential counterarguments, which makes the essay feel somewhat superficial.	0.9	0	\N	\N	1772831223.0518641
