How can a machine be a nurse and care for a sick patient? It cannot. But hospitals will use them anyway to save a quick buck, and patient care will become a horrific nightmare. In conclusion, artificial intelligence is a catastrophic threat to human employment and survival. We must immediately outlaw the development of any computer program that mimics human thought and go back to doing things the old-fashioned way before we are all replaced by our own creations.	2	This essay scored 2 out of 6 due to its lack of coherent argument structure, failure to provide concrete evidence or reasoning to support its claims, and the presence of inflammatory and emotive language that is characteristic of a personal opinion piece rather than a critical thinking essay. The writer's assertion that AI will "steal every single job on the planet" is an unsubstantiated and sweeping statement that demonstrates a disregard for the complexity of the topic. Additionally, the author's dismissal of opposing viewpoints with a pejorative term ("a greedy fool") is unprofessional and detracts from the intellectual credibility of the essay.	0.9	0	\N	\N	1772849083.9234035
ESSAY_1772849117_951	5	The rapid advancement of artificial intelligence (AI) has ignited a fierce global debate regarding its long-term impact on the job market. While alarmists predict a dystopian future characterized by mass unemployment, and techno-optimists foresee a utopian era of boundless leisure, a critical analysis suggests a much more complex and transitional reality. Rather than causing the wholesale elimination of human labor, AI is poised to act as a profound catalyst for economic restructuring, necessitating a critical shift in workforce skills and education.\n\nTo understand the potential trajectory of AI, it is highly instructive to examine historical precedents. During the Industrial Revolution, the automation of textile manufacturing caused severe localized displacement for artisanal weavers. However, it ultimately generated unprecedented job growth in machine manufacturing, maintenance, and entirely new consumer markets. Similarly, AI will undoubtedly render certain routine, predictable tasks obsolete—particularly in sectors like data entry, basic customer service, and rudimentary logistical planning. Acknowledging this inevitable displacement is vital, as ignoring it minimizes the very real economic pain that specific demographics will experience in the short term.\n\nConversely, the assumption that AI is merely a job destroyer fundamentally misunderstands the nature of technological innovation. By significantly reducing the cost of intelligence and analysis, AI will lower barriers to entry for countless industries, spurring economic growth. It will create entirely new categories of employment that are difficult to conceptualize today, much as the advent of the internet created millions of jobs in web design, digital marketing, and cybersecurity. Furthermore, AI is increasingly functioning as an augmentation tool rather than a strict replacement. In fields such as medicine and law, AI can process vast datasets to assist human professionals in making more accurate diagnoses or building stronger legal strategies, thereby increasing the value of human judgment and empathy rather than replacing it.\n\nUltimately, the true challenge presented by AI is not a permanent shortage of jobs, but a temporary, albeit severe, mismatch of skills. The transition will require proactive, large-scale investments in reskilling programs, both by private corporations and public educational institutions. In conclusion, framing the AI revolution as a simple binary of job creation versus job destruction is a false dichotomy. The future labor market will not lack human workers, but it will absolutely demand a workforce capable of collaborating alongside advanced technological systems.	5	This essay scored 5 out of 6 because it effectively employs a nuanced perspective on the AI-induced job market transformation, striking a balance between optimism and alarm. Additionally, the author's use of transition words and phrases ("rather than," "a critical shift") helps to enhance the coherence and flow of the essay. \n\nThe only deduction comes from a minor point - the essay could benefit from a more precise thesis statement that explicitly highlights the main argument, which might make the introduction more impactful and clear in its intent.	0.9	0	\N	\N	1772849117.9173698
